Head over to the Link in Bio to watch the full series! ⁠

@nnieguglia is a Professional Skateboarder from Montreal, Canada. Rather than hitting the same spots all year, Annie decided to head to Colorado in her RV taking in the open space, colors, and concrete skateparks. 

We joined Annie for a few days on and off the grid with her friend @alexisfortin83 to hit some of Colorado's best skateparks. Between skating and meeting with friends, Annie and Alexis head off the grid to cook, camp, and enjoy the beauty of the Rocky Mountains.

Presented by @therealgorv! 

More at http://bit.ly/Boundless-Ep-5 

#GORV #ROAM #BOUNDLESS #RV

Griff Washburn aka @GothBabemusic is a Musician, Surfer, and Climber.  Rather than going to the same recording studio, Griff built one in his RV allowing him to put music secondary and live life to the fullest.

We Joined Griff for a weekend off the grid with his partner Cate and dog, Sadie to explore his songwriting process, love for rock climbing, and source of inspiration. Seeking adventure and a one of a kind view of Mt. Hood, we joined the crew on French's Dome for a day of climbing and music.

Our new Roam Academy course - second in a six-part series focused on the RV lifestyle - is ‘Adventure Inspired Cooking 102' with endurance athlete and classically-trained Chef @lentinealexis HEAD TO THE LINK IN OUR PROFILE TO WATCH FOR FREE, courtesy of our wonderful partner @gorving . ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
In this class, Lentine delves into some of her favorite recipes. Let the spirit of your adventures inspire your creativity in the kitchen (or at the campsite!) and use recipes that help you tune into nature. Lentine teaches you her tactical skills, how she stocks her RV, and how to make her delicious recipes from breakfast to dinner and everything in between. Free downloadable recipes are available for all of her recipes. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
As Lentine says, “food and the knowledge of what fuels us has the power to unlock our wildest dreams, greatest potential and ultimate joy.” Let the spirit of your adventures inspire your creativity in the kitchen (or at the campsite!) and use recipes that help you tune into nature.

Newday Impact’s Ocean Health Portfolio focuses on Clean Coasts, Coral Conservation, Marine Wildlife and Plastic Removal. node.text:
We’re proud to announce we’ve become an Alliance Member for See Change Sessions @seechangesessions — a 2-day virtual summit August 18-19 on the intersection of climate action, sustainable business & the outdoor sports ecosystem. The event is designed to connect passionate intra & entrepreneurs that want to protect our outdoor playgrounds. It raises funds for a great org — Parley for the Oceans @parley.tv ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
The summit will host some amazing speakers like: Laird Hamilton @lairdhamiltonsurf (Big Wave Surfer / Innovator), Tony Fadell (iPod Inventor, Nest Founder), Pippa Ehrlich @the_rewilding (Academy-Award Winner for Best Documentary in 2021 for My Octopus Teacher), Captain Paul Watson (Founder of Greenpeace), Tina Liselius (Brand Communications Director, Thule), Dr. Wallace J. Nichols (Author, Marine Biologist), Cyrill Gutsch (Founder & CEO of Parley for the Oceans), Ryan Harris (Owner & Founder, Earth Tech Surf)...and a ton more from diverse fields — scientists, engineers, investors, activists, athletes, and others. ⁠⁠

We’re also giving away free admission to the first 6 people to comment “I want to See Change” below ⬇️
